CreateGroupMembership.description: Add a QuickSight user to a QuickSight group.

CreateIAMPolicyAssignment.name: CreateIAMPolicyAssignment
CreateIAMPolicyAssignment.description:
Creates an assignment with one specified IAM Policy ARN that will be assigned to specified
                                                groups or users of QuickSight.

CreateNamespace.name: CreateNamespace
CreateNamespace.description: Grants permission to create an QuickSight namespace

CreateReader.name: CreateReader
CreateReader.description: CreateReader enables the user to provision Amazon QuickSight readers.

DeleteGroupMembership.description: Remove a user from a group so that he/she is no longer a member of the group.

DeleteNamespace.name: DeleteNamespace
DeleteNamespace.description: Grants permission to delete a QuickSight namespace

DeleteTemplateAlias.name: DeleteTemplateAlias
DeleteTemplateAlias.description: Deletes the item that the specified template alias points to

DeleteThemeAlias.name: DeleteThemeAlias
DeleteThemeAlias.description: Deletes the item that the specified theme alias points to

DeleteUser.description:
Delete the QuickSight user that is associated with the identity of the IAM user/role
                                                making the call. The IAM user is not deleted as a result of this call.

DeleteUserByPrincipalId.name: DeleteUserByPrincipalId
DeleteUserByPrincipalId.description: Deletes a user identified by its principal ID.

DescribeAccountCustomization.description: Grants permission to describe an account customization for QuickSight account or namespace

DescribeAccountSettings.description: Grants permission to describe the administrative account settings for QuickSight account

DescribeCustomPermissions.name: DescribeCustomPermissions
DescribeCustomPermissions.description: Grants permission to describe a custom permissions resource in a QuickSight account

DescribeDashboard.name: DescribeDashboard
DescribeDashboard.description: Provides a summary for a dashboard

DescribeDashboardPermissions.name: DescribeDashboardPermissions
DescribeDashboardPermissions.description: Describes read and write permissions for a dashboard

DescribeGroup.name: DescribeGroup
DescribeGroup.description: Return a QuickSight group’s description and ARN.

DescribeNamespace.name: DescribeNamespace
DescribeNamespace.description: Grants permission to describe a QuickSight namespace

DescribeTemplateAlias.name: DescribeTemplateAlias
DescribeTemplateAlias.description: Describes the template alias for a template

DescribeThemePermissions.description: Describes read and write permissions on a theme

DescribeUser.name: DescribeUser
DescribeUser.description: Return information about a user, given the user name.

GetAuthCode.name: GetAuthCode
GetAuthCode.description: Return an auth code representing a QuickSight user.

GetDashboardEmbedUrl.name: GetDashboardEmbedUrl
GetDashboardEmbedUrl.description: Return a QuickSight dashboard embedding URL.

GetGroupMapping.name: GetGroupMapping
GetGroupMapping.description:
GetGroupMapping is used only in Amazon QuickSight Enterprise edition accounts. It
                                                enables the user to use Amazon QuickSight to identify and display the Microsoft Active
                                                Directory (Microsoft Active Directory) directory groups that are mapped to roles in
                                                Amazon QuickSight.

GetSessionEmbedUrl.name: GetSessionEmbedUrl
GetSessionEmbedUrl.description: Grants permission to get a URL to embed QuickSight console experience.

ListCustomPermissions.name: ListCustomPermissions
ListCustomPermissions.description: Grants permission to list custom permissions resources in QuickSight account

ListDashboardVersions.name: ListDashboardVersions
ListDashboardVersions.description: Lists all the versions of the dashboards in the QuickSight subscription

ListDashboards.name: ListDashboards
ListDashboards.description: Lists dashboards in an AWS account

ListGroupMemberships.name: ListGroupMemberships
ListGroupMemberships.description: Return a list of member users in a group.

ListGroups.description: Get a list of all user groups in QuickSight.

ListIAMPolicyAssignments.name: ListIAMPolicyAssignments
ListIAMPolicyAssignments.description: List all assignments in the current Amazon QuickSight account.

ListIAMPolicyAssignmentsForUser.name: ListIAMPolicyAssignmentsForUser

ListTagsForResource.name: ListTagsForResource
ListTagsForResource.description: List tags of a QuickSight resource.

ListTemplateAliases.name: ListTemplateAliases
ListTemplateAliases.description: Lists all the aliases of a template

ListTemplateVersions.description: Lists all the versions of the templates in the current Amazon QuickSight account

ListThemeVersions.name: ListThemeVersions

ListThemes.description: Lists all the themes in the current Amazon QuickSight account

ListUserGroups.name: ListUserGroups
ListUserGroups.description: Return a list of groups that a given user is a member of.

ListUsers.name: ListUsers
ListUsers.description: Return a list of all of the QuickSight users belonging to this account.

RegisterUser.name: RegisterUser
RegisterUser.description:
Create a QuickSight user, whose identity is associated with the IAM identity/role
                                                specified in the request.

SearchDirectoryGroups.name: SearchDirectoryGroups
SearchDirectoryGroups.description:
SearchDirectoryGroups is used only in Amazon QuickSight Enterprise edition accounts.
                                                It enables the user to use Amazon QuickSight to display your Microsoft Active Directory
                                                directory groups so that you can choose which ones to map to roles in Amazon QuickSight.

SetGroupMapping.name: SetGroupMapping
SetGroupMapping.description:
SearchDirectoryGroups is used only in Amazon QuickSight Enterprise edition accounts.
                                                It enables the user to use Amazon QuickSight to display your Microsoft Active Directory
                                                directory groups so that you can choose which ones to map to roles in Amazon QuickSight.

Subscribe.name: Subscribe
Subscribe.description:
Subscribe enables the user to subscribe to Amazon QuickSight. Enabling this action
                                                also allows the user to upgrade the subscription to Enterprise edition.

TagResource.name: TagResource
TagResource.description: Add tags to a QuickSight resource

Unsubscribe.name: Unsubscribe
Unsubscribe.description:
Unsubscribe enables the user to unsubscribe from Amazon QuickSight, which permanently
                                                deletes all users and their resources from Amazon QuickSight.

UntagResource.name: UntagResource
UntagResource.description: Remove tags from a QuickSight resource.
